{{Infobox language |name=Abidji |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |ethnicity=[[Abidji people|Abidji]] |speakers={{sigfig|50500|2}} |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Kwa languages|Kwa]] |iso3=abi |glotto=abid1235 |glottorefname=Abidji }} '''Abidji''' (Abiji) is a language of uncertain classification within the [[Kwa language|Kwa]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] family. It is spoken in [[Ivory Coast]].
