[[File:Western Moroccan Arabic Map.PNG|thumb|right|Map showing Western Moroccan Arabic speaking areas (yellow)]]
'''Western Morocco Arabic''', '''Western Moroccan Arabic''' or '''ʿAroubi Arabic''' is a [[dialectal continuum]] of [[Hilalian dialects|Hilalian]] [[Varieties of Arabic|Arabic]], mainly spoken in the plains of western ([[Doukkala-Abda|Doukkala, Abda]], [[Tadla]], [[Chaouia (Morocco)|Chaouia]], [[Rhamna]], [[Sraghna]], [[Chiadma]] and [[Zaër]]) and central-western ([[Saïss]], [[Gharb-Chrarda-Béni Hssen|Gharb]] and [[pre-Rif]]) plains of [[Morocco]].<ref name="Elhimer1">M. El Himer, [http://elhimer.com/images/publications/zones.pdf Zones linguistiques du Maroc arabophone : contacts et effets à Salé], in: Between the Atlantic and Indian Oceans, Studies on Contemporary Arabic, 7th AIDA Conference, 2006, held in Vienna</ref>

It can be divided into 3 [[regiolect]]s : northern, central and southern.<ref name="ElHimer2">M. El Himer, [http://www.elhimer.com/images/publications/variation%20linguistique%20am.pdf Variations linguistiques de l’arabe marocain: de la démarcation régionale à la neutralisation urbaine] (unpublished)</ref> 

